The paper focuses on object detection in images and videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of dual refinement networks and deformable detection heads suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also emphasizes the importance of achieving high accuracy in real time, which suggests a focus on optimization and performance (cs.LG). The application of the proposed methods to underwater object detection and grasping suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of videos in the evaluation of the proposed methods suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
